Bethphage, interpreted house of the mouth or house of the jaw, which was a village of priests, was a type of confession, and it was situated on the Mount of Olives, where there is the light of knowledge, where there is rest from labor and suffering. 

"Then sent Jesus two disciples." Not without cause can the two disciples sent to bring the beasts to the Lord be understood to signify two orders of preaches, one evidently for the Gentiles, another directed to the circumcised. Properly two are sent, whether to set forth knowledge of the truth and purity of action, or by means of a double love, evidently of God and of neighbor, that the mystery might be proclaimed to the whole world.

